{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"DOMMatrixReadOnly: flipX() method","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrixReadOnly/flipX","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","browserCompat":["api.DOMMatrixReadOnly.flipX"],"sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Geometry_interfaces\">Geometry interfaces</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrixReadOnly\"><code>DOMMatrixReadOnly</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrixReadOnly/DOMMatrixReadOnly\"><code>DOMMatrixReadOnly()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Instance methods</summary><ol><li><em><code>flipX()</code> </em></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrixReadOnly/scale\"><code>scale()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrixReadOnly/translate\"><code>translate()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Geometry Interfaces</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrix\"><code>DOMMatrix</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMPoint\"><code>DOMPoint</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMPointReadOnly\"><code>DOMPointReadOnly</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMQuad\"><code>DOMQuad</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMRect\"><code>DOMRect</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMRectReadOnly\"><code>DOMRectReadOnly</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","sidebarMacro":"APIRef","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <code>flipX()</code> method of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrixReadOnly\"><code>DOMMatrixReadOnly</code></a> interface creates a new matrix being the result of the original matrix flipped about the x-axis.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>  DOMMatrixReadOnly<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">flipX</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Returns a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrix\"><code>DOMMatrix</code></a> containing a new matrix being the result of the original matrix flipped about the x-axis, which is equivalent to multiplying the matrix by <code>DOMMatrix(-1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0)</code>. The original matrix is not modified.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"inverting_a_triangle","title":"Inverting a triangle","isH3":true,"content":"<p>In this example, the SVG contains two paths in the shape of a triangle, both drawn to the same position. Note that the x co-ordinate of the viewBox attribute is negative, showing us content from both sides of the x-axis.</p>\n<p>The JavaScript first creates an identity matrix, then uses the <code>flipX()</code> method to create a new matrix, which is then applied to the blue triangle, inverting it across the x-axis. The red triangle is left in place.</p>\n<h4 id=\"html\">HTML</h4>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">html</span></p><pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>svg</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">width</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>100<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">height</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>100<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">viewBox</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>-50 0 100 100<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>path</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">fill</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>red<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">d</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>M 0 50 L 50 0 L 50 100 Z<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/&gt;</span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>path</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">id</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>flipped<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">fill</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>blue<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">d</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>M 0 50 L 50 0 L 50 100 Z<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>svg</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h4 id=\"javascript\">JavaScript</h4>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> flipped <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getElementById</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"flipped\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> matrix <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">DOMMatrixReadOnly</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> flippedMatrix <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> matrix<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">flipX</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nflipped<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">setAttribute</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"transform\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> flippedMatrix<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">toString</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<h4 id=\"result\">Result</h4><div class=\"code-example\" id=\"sect1\"><p class=\"example-header\"></p><iframe class=\"sample-code-frame\" title=\"Inverting a triangle sample\" id=\"frame_inverting_a_triangle\" src=\"http://localhost:5042/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrixReadOnly/flipX/runner.html?id=inverting_a_triangle\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://drafts.fxtf.org/geometry/#dom-dommatrixreadonly-flipx","title":"Geometry Interfaces Module Level 1"}],"query":"api.DOMMatrixReadOnly.flipX"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.DOMMatrixReadOnly.flipX"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The flipX() method of the DOMMatrixReadOnly interface creates a new matrix being the result of the original matrix flipped about the x-axis.","popularity":0,"modified":"2023-04-07T05:52:28.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/dommatrixreadonly/flipx","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/main/files/en-us/web/api/dommatrixreadonly/flipx/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/41a8b9c9832359d445d136b6d7a8a28737badc6b","filename":"index.md"},"short_title":"flipX()","parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"References"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrixReadOnly","title":"DOMMatrixReadOnly"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrixReadOnly/flipX","title":"flipX()"}],"pageTitle":"DOMMatrixReadOnly: flipX() method - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}